tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE fashion_photography_license_agreements (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  photographer_name VARCHAR(255),
  client_name VARCHAR(255),
  license_type VARCHAR(100),
  contract_date DATE,
  expiration_date DATE,
  usage_rights TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE PhotographyLicenses (
    license_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_name TEXT,
    client_name TEXT,
    license_type TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE UsageRightsContracts (
    contract_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    license_id INT,
    restriction TEXT,
    authorizations TEXT,
    CONSTRAINT FK_license_id FOREIGN KEY (license_id) REFERENCES PhotographyLicenses(license_id)
);

CREATE TABLE fashion_photography_license_agreements (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_name VARCHAR(255),
    client_name VARCHAR(255),
    agreement_date DATE,
    license_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE photography_contracts (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    contract_number VARCHAR(50),
    photographer_id INT,
    client_id INT,
    contract_date DATE,
    contract_terms TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE usage_rights (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    agreement_id INT,
    usage_description TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE agreements (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	photographer_id INT,
	client_id INT,
	agreement_date DATE,
	valid_from DATE,
	valid_until DATE
);

CREATE TABLE contracts (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	agreement_id INT,
	contract_type VARCHAR(50),
	terms TEXT,
	signature_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE usage_rights (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	contract_id INT,
	photograph_id INT,
	usage_type VARCHAR(50),
	license_terms TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE photographs (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	photographer_id INT,
	image_url VARCHAR(255),
	resolution VARCHAR(20),
	capture_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE fashion_photography_license_agreements (
    agreement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_name VARCHAR(100),
    client_name VARCHAR(100),
    agreement_date DATE,
    license_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE contract_details (
    contract_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agreement_id INT,
    contract_date DATE,
    contract_terms TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (agreement_id) REFERENCES fashion_photography_license_agreements(agreement_id)
);

CREATE TABLE usage_rights (
    rights_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agreement_id INT,
    usage_name VARCHAR(50),
    restriction_details TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (agreement_id) REFERENCES fashion_photography_license_agreements(agreement_id)
);
